Overall Markup: Gross Margin = (sales - cost of good sold) / sales
Is the company controlling overall expenses well? SG&A-to-Sales = SG&A Expense / Sales
How does operating contribute to overall sales? Operating Margin = Operating Income / Sales
How is financing impacting sales? Interest Expense-to-Sales = Interest Expense / Sales
How does Tax impact? Effective Tax Rate = Income Taxes / Pre-Tax Income
How much profit is earned on each dollar of sales? -> Profit Margin Ratio
Account Receivable Turnover = Sales / Average Account Receivable
Inventory Turnover = Cost of Good Sold / Average Inventory
Purchase = ending inventory + COGS - beginning inventory
Account Payable Turnover = Purchases / Avg. Account Payable
Fixed Asset Turnover = Sales / Avg. Net Property, Plant, Equipment (PP&E)
How much sales are generated using available assets? -> Asset Turnover Ratios (How many times per year do we cycle through accounts?)
Days Receivable Outstanding = 365 * (Avg A/R / Sales)
Days Inventory = 365 * (Avg Inventory / CoGS)
Days Payable = 365 * (Avg AP / Purchases)
Net Trade Cycle = Days Receivable + Days Inventory - Days Payable

A difference interpretation -> Days Outstanding Ratio (how many days, on average, are accounts outstanding?) -> Net Trade Cycle -> how much short term $ the company need to borrow to balance cash in and out.
